Chilean Stocks: CCU, Concha y Toro, Empresas La Polar and Paz

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-08-05T21:00:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/chilean-stocks-ccu-concha-y-toro-la-polar-parque-arauco-paz.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 1.8 percent to 4,066.09.  Cia. Cervecerias Unidas SA (CCU CC) rose 2.7 percent to
4,948.1 pesos. Chile’s largest brewer was reiterated at “buy”
at Bank of America Corp., which cited “compelling valuations.”  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   fell 1.3 percent to
478.36 pesos. The Chilean department-store operator under
investigation for consumer loan irregularities said it may
recover as much as 226 billion pesos ($486 million) of sales on
credit as of May 31, according to a filing sent to regulators
yesterday. This represents 54 percent of the company’s
receivables as of March 31, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg.  Paz Corp SA (PAZ)   fell 1.4 percent to 305.62 pesos, its
fourth day of losses. The real estate developer posted a 27
percent fall in profits in the second quarter to 1.16 billion
pesos, according to a regulatory filing.  Vina Concha & Toro SA (CONCHA CC),  Chile ’s largest wine
exporter, fell 0.2 percent to 968.92 pesos. Chilean wine exports
posted an 8 percent fall in volumes in June, according to a
statement from wine producers association Vinas de Chile.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
